 kollektive Gedächtnis, insbesondere im China unter Xi Jinping, eine langanhaltende zentrale politische Herausforderung für die nachhaltige Stabilisierung der Herrschaftslegitimation der KPCh darstellt.  afunded by Freie Universität Berlin  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aGeschichtspolitik der KPCh. 4aKampf gegen das Vergessen. 4ahistorischer Nihilismus. 4akonkurrierende Narrative. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh2 aFreie Universität Berlinefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z97831107538510 cEPUBz97831107194060 cprintz978311071781540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110719253zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110719253zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110719253.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075385-1 EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA